<style>
  .luna-faq {
    background: var(--gr-cream, #f5f0e8);
    padding: 64px 16px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.05);
  }

  .luna-faq__container {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .luna-faq__title {
    font-size: 30px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--gr-dark, #1a1a1a);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .luna-faq__subtitle {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--gr-sage, #7c8c78);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .luna-faq__item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.15);
  }

  .luna-faq__question {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 20px 0;
    text-align: left;
    cursor: pointer;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    font-family: inherit;
  }

  .luna-faq__question-text {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--gr-dark, #1a1a1a);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .luna-faq__question-icon {
    font-size: 24px;
    color: var(--gr-dark, #1a1a1a);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
    user-select: none;
  }

  .luna-faq__answer {
    padding-bottom: 20px;
    margin-top: -4px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--gr-sage, #7c8c78);
    line-height: 1.7;
    display: none;
  }

  .luna-faq__answer--open {
    display: block;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .luna-faq {
      padding: 80px 24px;
    }

    .luna-faq__title {
      font-size: 36px;
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .luna-faq__container {
      max-width: 780px;
    }
  }
</style>

<section class="luna-faq" data-section-type="luna-faq-kids">
  <div class="luna-faq__container">
    <h2 class="luna-faq__title">Parents ask, we answer.</h2>
    <p class="luna-faq__subtitle">Everything you need to know before protecting your little ones.</p>

    <div data-faq-list>
      <div class="luna-faq__item" data-faq-item>
        <button class="luna-faq__question" data-faq-toggle>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-text">What age is this safe for?</span>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-icon" data-faq-icon>+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="luna-faq__answer" data-faq-answer>
          Luna Naturals Kids patches are safe for children ages 2 and up. The patches stick to clothing, not skin, so there's zero direct skin contact with active ingredients. Always consult your pediatrician if you have concerns about specific allergies.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="luna-faq__item" data-faq-item>
        <button class="luna-faq__question" data-faq-toggle>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-text">Are these really DEET-free?</span>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-icon" data-faq-icon>+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="luna-faq__answer" data-faq-answer>
          100% DEET-free. We use only plant-based citronella and eucalyptus essential oils. No parabens, no phthalates, no synthetic chemicals. Just natural protection that actually works.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="luna-faq__item" data-faq-item>
        <button class="luna-faq__question" data-faq-toggle>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-text">Can my child put them on by themselves?</span>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-icon" data-faq-icon>+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="luna-faq__answer" data-faq-answer>
          Yes! That's the beauty of it. Kids as young as 3 can peel and stick the patches on their own clothes. Most kids think they're fun stickers and actually ask to wear them.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="luna-faq__item" data-faq-item>
        <button class="luna-faq__question" data-faq-toggle>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-text">How many patches does my child need?</span>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-icon" data-faq-icon>+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="luna-faq__answer" data-faq-answer>
          1-2 patches per child provides full coverage. Stick them on the collar, sleeve, or shorts near exposed skin. For heavy mosquito areas, use 2 patches on opposite sides of the body.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="luna-faq__item" data-faq-item>
        <button class="luna-faq__question" data-faq-toggle>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-text">Will they stay on during sports and swimming?</span>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-icon" data-faq-icon>+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="luna-faq__answer" data-faq-answer>
          The patches are waterproof and sweatproof. They'll stay on through soccer practice, sprinklers, and playground time. For full submersion swimming, reapply after drying off.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="luna-faq__item" data-faq-item>
        <button class="luna-faq__question" data-faq-toggle>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-text">What if my child has sensitive skin or eczema?</span>
          <span class="luna-faq__question-icon" data-faq-icon>+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="luna-faq__answer" data-faq-answer>
          Because the patches go on clothing &mdash; not skin &mdash; they're ideal for kids with sensitive skin, eczema, or allergies to topical products. The active oils evaporate into the air around the patch, creating a protective zone without skin contact.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
(function() {
  var section = document.querySelector('[data-section-type="luna-faq-kids"]');
  if (!section) return;

  var items = section.querySelectorAll('[data-faq-item]');
  var currentOpen = null;

  items.forEach(function(item, idx) {
    var toggle = item.querySelector('[data-faq-toggle]');
    var answer = item.querySelector('[data-faq-answer]');
    var icon = item.querySelector('[data-faq-icon]');

    toggle.addEventListener('click', function() {
      if (currentOpen === idx) {
        answer.classList.remove('luna-faq__answer--open');
        icon.textContent = '+';
        currentOpen = null;
      } else {
        /* Close previous */
        if (currentOpen !== null) {
          var prevItem = items[currentOpen];
          prevItem.querySelector('[data-faq-answer]').classList.remove('luna-faq__answer--open');
          prevItem.querySelector('[data-faq-icon]').textContent = '+';
        }
        answer.classList.add('luna-faq__answer--open');
        icon.textContent = '\u2212';
        currentOpen = idx;
      }
    });
  });
})();
</script>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Luna FAQ Kids",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "luna-faq-kids-section",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
